The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. The proposed method involves the use of a CNN backbone and graph convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves learning discriminative features and alignment, which falls under the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of topology information and graph matching also suggests the possibility of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) being a relevant sub-category. The paper also involves experiments on datasets, which suggests the possibility of cs.MM (Multimedia) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with occlusion and robustness, which suggests the possibility of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) being a relevant sub-category.
